section.section:
An initial report:
May be:
Oral if followed by a written report within 5 working days from the date of the death; or
Written;
Shall contain the following relevant information:
The name, age, and sex of the deceased;
The time of discovery of the death;
The deceased's place of residence at the time of death;
The location of the body at the time of discovery;
The place where the body was found;
The name of the person who took custody of the body;
The name of the person evaluating the death, if known;
Whether or not an autopsy is being performed, if known; and
The name, address, and telephone number of the next of kin or legal guardian, if known; and
Shall contain any other information the administrative head of the facility determines should be provided to the medical examiner and the persons listed in paragraph (1) of this subsection on the deaths occurring:
By violence;
By suicide;
By casualty;
Suddenly, if the deceased was in apparent good health; or
In any suspicious or unusual manner.

At a minimum, the status report shall note:
The number of deaths;
The location of each death;
The cause of each death, if known; and
Other data the Secretary determines to be relevant to the status report.
